name: Justin L Word
text: The best part of Orange beach for me. If you are the laid back type that doesn’t enjoy the over crowded condominiums and public beaches Ono is a great spot to have a home. Being only forty five minutes from Fairhope we try to head down as much as we can. They have a great love for nature and preserve night time for what it should be, dark so we can see the stars in the sky.

name: Amelia Blackwood
text: What's not to love? The privacy & serenity of the island is enough to make you never want to leave...enjoy every time & always look forward to my next getaway.  Of course there are amenities in abundance as soon as you cross the bridge but meanwhile it's a solitude of paradise.

name: Path to Manliness
text:
This "private island" is a joke. It is anything but prestigious. They let hundreds of contractors onto the island nearly every day. Some of them are illegals. Their trucks block the only major road on the island basically every day. The unarmed guards at the gate are nice but they are toothless and simply the illusion of security. As an owner, I received a ticket for a going through a stop sign, which I clearly did not do. The island cannot budget money and they need to raise funds for repairing the only bridge on the island. The POA fees are way too low so they have budgeting problems, yet the island is too cheap to raise their fees, so they'll nickel and dime you for petty little nuisances.

There is also a coyote infestation on this island and they have been killing small pets of owners. I once had a coyote follow me as I was walking my dog. Hardly a place to relax. This has been an ongoing issue for at least a year, with little to nothing being done to remedy the situation.

Find a better place to live.
